By Rita Okoye Rihanna is pregnant with second child. The 34-year-old singer revealed the big news as she performed at the 2023 Super Bowl Halftime last night. The already proud mother of one took the stage dressed head-to-toe in bright red, revealing a baby bump, and becoming the first pregnant woman to star in the halftime show. During the performance of her song “Bitches Better Have My Money,” the singer rubbed her stomach on stage in front of delighted attendees. A rep for the singer also confirmed that she is pregnant with baby number two. The Grammy winner and her beau, rapper A$AP Rocky, welcomed their first child in May 2022.